    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Shading Coverage</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Melissa Sapio letter responds to recent article on NBC sportscaster Bob Costas and network's coverage of Olympic Games</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Does anyone really care about Bob Costas's hair color? What in the world could be less interesting than learning about lighting on his set and color enhancements making his brown hair appear red? Tell me something more -- like the horrible ratings NBC was getting for its storytelling style.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Does anyone really care about Bob Costas's hair color? What in the world could be less interesting than learning about lighting on his set and color enhancements making his brown hair appear red? Tell me something more -- like the horrible ratings NBC was getting for its storytelling style.</p>
        <p>Your information about the ''lovely auburn highlights'' of Costas was as ridiculous as the irrelevant fluff NBC has been supplying viewers with (such as John Glenn's connection to Australia). Shouldn't the Olympics be more than this? Maybe it should be about the athletes.</p>
        <p>MELISSA SAPIO  Kinnelon, N.J.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
